cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.SI 

This paper presents a new approach and architecture for learning compact and efficient deep neural networks, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SD). The proposed method is applied to 1D convolutional neural networks for audio classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the weight sampling approach and induced WSNet promote parameter sharing, which is also relevant to information theory (cs.SI).
